OL,3,CCaptain of container ship in North Sea
OL,4,Ccrash denies manslaughter
OL,6,FThe captain of the container ship
OL,7,Fwhich crashed into a US oil tanker in
OL,8,Fthe North Sea has pleaded not guilty
OL,9,Fto manslaughter.
OL,11,FThe Solong's master, Vladimir Motin,
OL,12,F59, of Primorsky, St Petersburg, is
OL,13,Faccused of the unlawful killing of
OL,14,Fcrew member Mark Angelo Pernia, 38, in
OL,15,Fthe collision off the East Yorkshire
OL,16,Fcoast.
OL,18,FOn Friday, Motin appeared at the Old
OL,19,FBailey by videolink from HMP Hull for
OL,20,Fa plea hearing before Judge Mark
OL,21,FLucraft KC.
