OL,3,CCaptain of container ship in North Sea
OL,4,Ccrash denies manslaughter
OL,6,FThe 140m-long Solong is Portuguese-
OL,7,Fregistered and was carrying about 157
OL,8,Fcontainers.
OL,10,FThe Stena Immaculate is 183m long and
OL,11,Fwas carrying jet fuel. It anchored at
OL,12,Fthe point of the collision about 15
OL,13,Fhours before the impact.
OL,15,FThe Solong was travelling at about 15
OL,16,Fknots when it hit the port side of the
OL,17,Fother vessel.
